comment: Smith (HOU) does not make contact with Love (CLE) as he attempts the layup.
Smith (CLE) makes contact with the body of Harden (HOU) and the contact affects his movement to the basket.
Ariza (HOU) makes contact with the shoulder of James (CLE) while trying to strip the ball from behind.
Jones (HOU) makes contact with the arm of Thompson (CLE) causing him to lose control of the rebound.
Smith (HOU) loses the ball as he goes up for the shot in the paint.
Jones (HOU) maintains verticality on drive by James (CLE).
Thompson (CLE) makes contact to the head of Jones (HOU) from behind on the jump shot.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the foul was confirmed to have taken place prior to the shot clock expiring.
James (CLE) knocks the ball away from Harden (HOU) as he tries to split the perimeter trap.
Harden (HOU) walks into space occupied by James (CLE). Contact escalates and should have resulted in a double personal foul.
Smith (HOU) plays legal defense on the drive to the basket by James (CLE.
Ariza (HOU) and Thompson (CLE) lock up to start, but release prior to attempting the rebound.
Love (CLE) makes contact with the arm of Smith (HOU) and the contact affects his movement to the basket.
As Harden (HOU) starts his drive to the basket, he clamps the arm of James (CLE) and an offensive foul should have been called.
After the initial hook by Harden (HOU), James (CLE) fouls by pulling him. The foul causes Harden to lose his pivot foot.
Correctly called 24 Second Violation.
Smith (CLE) makes contact with the ball, causing Smith (HOU) to lose control.
While attempting to be vertical, Smith (HOU) jumps and turns into the James (CLE).
Smith (CLE) commits the take foul on Harden (HOU).
James (CLE) commits the take foul on Harden (HOU).

The free throw attempt is taken at 00.6 and the timeout awarded immediately after Smith (CLE) gains possession while in the air. A minimum of 00.3 must come off the game clock after the free throw attempt.
